  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Return the derivative of the specified order of a polynomial."
          },
          {
            "type": "directive",
            "name": "note",
            "body": "   This forms part of the old polynomial API. Since version 1.4, the\n   new polynomial API defined in `numpy.polynomial` is preferred.\n   A summary of the differences can be found in the\n   :doc:`transition guide </reference/routines.polynomials>`.",
            "raw": ".. note::\n   This forms part of the old polynomial API. Since version 1.4, the\n   new polynomial API defined in `numpy.polynomial` is preferred.\n   A summary of the differences can be found in the\n   :doc:`transition guide </reference/routines.polynomials>`."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "p",
            "type": "poly1d or sequence",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Polynomial to differentiate.\nA sequence is interpreted as polynomial coefficients, see `poly1d`."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "m",
            "type": "int, optional",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Order of differentiation (default: 1)"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "der",
            "type": "poly1d",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "A new polynomial representing the derivative."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The derivative of the polynomial :math:`x^3 + x^2 + x^1 + 1` is:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> p = np.poly1d([1,1,1,1])\n>>> p2 = np.polyder(p)\n>>> p2\npoly1d([3, 2, 1])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "which evaluates to:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> p2(2.)\n17.0"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "We can verify this, approximating the derivative with\n``(f(x + h) - f(x))/h``:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> (p(2. + 0.001) - p(2.)) / 0.001\n17.007000999997857"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The fourth-order derivative of a 3rd-order polynomial is zero:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.polyder(p, 2)\npoly1d([6, 2])\n>>> np.polyder(p, 3)\npoly1d([6])\n>>> np.polyder(p, 4)\npoly1d([0])"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "see-also",
        "title": "See Also",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "polyint \u2014 Anti-derivative of a polynomial."
          },
